
				                 Two people died and nine others were injured when a bakkie veered off the R546 and rolled near Secunda in Mpumalanga on Saturday, paramedics said.
When ER24 paramedics arrived on scene some of the injured “were lying on the ground and others sat at the scene”, ER24 spokeswoman Ineke van Huyssteen said.
“Upon further assessment it was found that two people showed no signs of life. Nine others sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate and were transported by ER24 and other medical services on [the] scene to Evander Hospital for further medical care.”
